Source: pool
Section: net
Priority: optional
Maintainer: POOL Protocol Maintainers <pool-dev@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 13), dh-dkms, dkms
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/amosdavis/POOL

Package: pool-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, dkms, linux-headers-amd64 | linux-headers-generic
Description: POOL kernel module (DKMS)
 Protected Orchestrated Overlay Link — secure transport protocol
 implemented as a Linux kernel module. Uses DKMS to automatically
 build pool.ko for the running kernel on install and kernel upgrades.
 .
 Provides: IP Protocol 253 transport, ChaCha20-Poly1305 AEAD encryption,
 X25519 ECDH key exchange, ML-KEM-768 post-quantum hybrid handshake,
 multicast peer discovery, built-in telemetry, and atomic configuration.

Package: pool-tools
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: pool-dkms
Suggests: python3
Description: POOL userspace tools and daemons
 Userspace components for the POOL secure transport protocol:
 .
  * poolctl — CLI management tool
  * poold — userspace daemon
  * pool_bridge — TCP-to-POOL bridge proxy
  * pool_migrate — gradual TCP→POOL migration tool
  * pool_vault — encrypted distributed file vault
  * pool_relay — relay daemon with operator incentives
  * pool_test — protocol test harness
  * libpool_shim.so — transparent POSIX socket shim (LD_PRELOAD)
  * pool_exporter.py — Prometheus metrics exporter
 .
 Includes systemd service units for all daemons.
